    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="511"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d511">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.801 Wireless/104</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Representative <persName type="from">Schuyler O.
                            Bland</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-11">June 11,
                            1936</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have your letter of the 11th
                        instant<note n="8" xml:id="d511fn8">Not printed.</note> transmitting copy of
                    a note from the Belgian Embassy regarding S. 4619, amending the Communications
                    Act of 1934 and requiring radio installations on shipboard.</p>
                <p>The Committee yesterday decided to table this bill for the remainder of the
                        session;<note n="9" xml:id="d511fn9">This information was communicated on
                        June 11 by telephone to the interested Embassies and Legations.</note>
                    however, I am placing your letter and the accompanying note on file for further
                    consideration in the event the matter is taken up at a later date.</p>
                <p>Yours very sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">S. O. Bland</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
